%N A152072 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = the largest product of a partition of n into k positive integers (1 <= k <= n).
%C A152072 The optimal partition is P(n,k) = ([(n+i)/k] : 0 <= i < k).
%C A152072 The table also appears in the solution of a maximum problem in arithmetic considered by K. Mahler and J. Popken. - J. van de Lune and _Juan Arias-de-Reyna_, Jan 05 2012
%C A152072 T(n,k) is the number of ways to select k class representatives from the mod k partitioning of {1,2,...,n}. - _Dennis P. Walsh_, Nov 27 2012
%C A152072 T(n,k) is the maximum number of length-k longest common subsequences of a pair of length-n strings. - _Cees H. Elzinga_, Jun 08 2014
%D A152072 Cees H. Elzinga and M. Studer, Normalization of Distance and Similarity in Sequence Analysis in G. Ritschard & M. Studer (eds), Proceedings of the International Conference on Sequence Analysis and Related Methods, Lausanne, June 8-10, 2016, pp 445-468.
%D A152072 David W. Wilson, Posting to Sequence Fans mailing List, Mar 11 2009.
%H A152072 David W. Wilson, <a href="/A152072/b152072.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10011</a>
%H A152072 Zhiwei Lin, H. Wang, and C. H. Elzinga, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1609.04722">Concordance and the Smallest Covering Set of Preference Orderings</a>, arXiv preprint arXiv:1609.04722 [cs.AI], 2016.
%H A152072 K. Mahler and J. Popken, <a href="https://carmamaths.org/resources/mahler/docs/120.pdf">Over een Maximumprobleem uit de Rekenkunde</a> (in Dutch), (On a Maximum Problem in Arithmetic), Nieuw Archief voor Wiskunde (3) 1 (1953), 1-15.
%F A152072 T(n,k) = Product_{i=0..k-1} [(n+i)/k].
%F A152072 T(n,n-d) = 2^d = A000079(d) (d <= n/2).
%F A152072 MAX(1 <= k <= n, T(n,k)) = A000792(n).
%F A152072 T(n,k) = (ceiling(n/k))^(n mod k)*(floor(n/k))^(k-n mod k). - _Dennis P. Walsh_, Nov 27 2012
%F A152072 Sum_{k = 1..n} T(n,k) = A152074(n). - _David W. Wilson_, Jul 07 2016
